Enclosed please find your explanation of payment (EOP) for services rendered to Healthfirst members. The EOP details the adjudication of your claims filed with
Healthfirst. It is important that you thoroughly review this information.
Healthfirst maintains an internal claims review procedure intended to provide you with a prompt, fair and full investigation and resolution of your inquiries or complaints.
Providers who are dissatisfied with a claim determination made by Healthfirst must submit a written request for review and reconsideration with all supporting
documentation to Healthfirst within ninety (90) calendar days from the paid date on the provider's EOP. Written requests, including attachments, are accepted via the
Healthfirst provider website at www.healthfirst.org or may be sent by mail to the following location: Healthfirst Correspondence Unit, P.O. Box 958438, Lake Mary, FL
32795-8438. Requests should include the basis for reconsideration and provide supporting documentation, including a copy of the claim and EOP. Requests submitted
Except for Medicare providers, if you are a non-participating physician and wish to dispute Healthfirst's payment of your claim, you may be eligible to file a complaint
through the NYS Independent Dispute Resolution (IDR) process. Please visit www.healthfirst.org/idr for more information.
Non-contracted Medicare providers have the right to submit a request for reconsideration of a denial of payment. You have 60 calendar days from notification of denial
to file a reconsideration. With the request of reconsideration, you must include a signed Waiver of Liability form (WOL). The form is available at www.healthfirst.org/wol.
Healthfirst will not make payments for claims submitted that do not comply with the following policies:
Timely claim filing: In-network provider must file claims within 180 days of the date of service. Out-of-network providers must file claims according to
Authorization: Except for emergency services and treatment of urgent medical conditions, out-of-network providers are required to receive authorization prior
to providing services to Healthfirst members, whether or not Healthfirst providers referred the members. Contact Healthfirst's Utilization Management
Department at 1-888-394-4327 to request pre-authorization for out-of-network services.
For all electronic claims, Healthfirst utilizes the Healthcare clearinghouse and Ability, a free online service for providers who do not have claims submission software.
Claims submitted electronically receive a status report indicating which claims were accepted, rejected and/or are pending, and the amount paid on the claim once it has
been finalized. Claims submitted electronically must include all of the following:
1). Healthfirst Payer ID Number 80141 on each claim
2). Complete Healthfirst Member ID Numbers (see member ID card or monthly enrollment roster)
3). A National Provider Identifier (NPI) should reside in:
. 837 Professional (HCFA) - Loop 2310B Rendering Provider Secondary ID, Segment/Element NM109. NM108 must qualify with an XX (NPI).
. 837 Institutional (UB04) - Loop 2010AA Billing Provider, Segment/Element NM109. NM108 must qualify with an XX (NPI)
All payments for services provided to Healthfirst members constitute payment in full. In-network providers may not balance bill members for the difference between their
actual charges and the reimbursed amounts, except for applicable co-pays or co-insurance. Out-of-network providers who participate in the Medicaid or Medicare
program may not balance bill Healthfirst members.

If you have claim activity and see a check amount of $0.00, it may be that your account with Healthfirst Health Plan, inc ., Healthfirst PHSP, Inc ., and/or Healthfirst
Insurance Company, Inc. (together, "Healthfirst") is currently in a negative balance or that claims activity has resulted in payment denials. If your account is in a negative
balance, this can be caused by adjustments that have resulted in overpayments that are being recouped. The specific reasons for an adjustment would have been
communicated on prior overpayment recovery letters. Any payments will be applied directly towards the reduction of your current negative balance until it's satisfied, and
as a result you'll receive a $0.00 amount under a Notification of Non-Payment along with your Explanation of Payment (EOP).
